race.comment: KOOL KADE (6) ready for this trip now after he jumped quickly and gripped on to hold second over 1010m at Moruya. Drawn to stalk the leaders and has the right figures to take this out. NEFRADITE (9) smart filly who demolished the small field at her fourth race start over 1000m at the Sapphire Coast. Will have little trouble running the 1200m and will relish Caitlin Sinclair's 3kg claim again. Will be savaging the line late. EYE FOR STYLE (11) returned a much stronger filly when she stormed down the outside at start six for a slick victory over 1200m at Nowra. Can go on with it now and looks destined for stronger races. BURNT TO A CRISP (2) finished over the top of them on debut when saluting over 1000m at Wagga. Wasn't disgraced when three-weeks between runs finishing a close third over 1180m at Gundagai. Maps to get the right run.
